~ test_protection.he — protection tag ENFORCEMENT (Pass 14).
   Supersedes the Pass 11 version, which only tested that tags parsed.
   Now that Stage A / Step 3 (enforcement) is built, tags are no longer
   inert: a denied tag is a real, catchable runtime error.

   This file can't configure the entitlement checker itself (that's a
   Go-level call, not an HE-level one — see lang/eval/entitlement_test.go
   for checker unit tests). What this file proves is the HE-visible
   behavior under the RUNTIME DEFAULT, which is AlwaysDeny — fail closed.
   So: every #protected[N] call here is expected to be denied, and every
   denial is expected to be cleanly catchable via try/or. ~

make Car3 #protected [
  has: [
    speed is 200
  ]
  can: [
    drive [
      say "Vroom! (this should never print under AlwaysDeny)"
    ]
  ]
]

create Replay [
  can: [
    past20Seconds #protected1 [
      say "Replaying last 20 seconds (should never print)"
    ]
    freePreview [
      say "This is a free preview, anyone can see it"
    ]
  ]
]

create Store [
  can: [
    unlockSkin(name) #protected2 [
      say "Unlocking skin: {name} (should never print)"
    ]
    browseSkins [
      say "Browsing the skin catalog (free)"
    ]
  ]
]

~ ── Unprotected abilities run exactly as before — no change here ── ~
tell Replay to freePreview
tell Store to browseSkins
say "Unprotected abilities ran normally."

~ ── A whole-object tag (#protected on Car3) is denied, and catchable ── ~
try [
  tell Car3 to drive
] or (err) [
  say "Caught expected denial for Car3: {err}"
]

~ ── A per-ability tag (#protected1 on past20Seconds) is denied too ── ~
try [
  tell Replay to past20Seconds
] or (err) [
  say "Caught expected denial for past20Seconds: {err}"
]

~ ── Same for a tagged ability that takes arguments ── ~
try [
  tell Store to unlockSkin with "Golden Falcon"
] or (err) [
  say "Caught expected denial for unlockSkin: {err}"
]

~ ── Denial doesn't corrupt the runtime — normal code keeps working
   after a caught denial, in the same program ── ~
tell Replay to freePreview
say "Program continued normally after catching denials."

say "All protection enforcement tests passed!"
